a theological perspective, the volume makes use of a broadened conceptualization of "mestizaje," or mutual cultural exchange, to challenge the church to recognize the effects of racial and ethnic particularity in all theological construction.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aRace relationsxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aRace relations. 0aRacismxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aRacismzNorth America. 0aTheologyzLatin America. 0aTheologyzNorth America. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz978081477610040uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814777367.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814777367423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814777367/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK